Hello Jason,

As far as I know, the way to append meta-data for an openoffice element is
using "user defined attributes" in meta.xml. For example:

<meta:user-defined meta:name=3D"License Name">Attribution-ShareAlike
2.5</meta:user-defined>
<meta:user-defined meta:name=3D"License URL">
http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.5/</meta:user-defined>
...

I would like to append meta-data as a child element of <office:meta>
element, but I think there's no easy way to do this, I'm still checking it.
The ideal scenario would be if CC RDF was in ODF specification.

I'll keep you updated, but don't delay your project, there is a lot of
discussion and work to be done regarding this question yet. =3D)


Best,
Cassio


